<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1704,1802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[277,384,1704,1730]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
where it is relatively widespread on dolerite mountains, especially in the central highlands. Its anatomical and chemical characteristics suggest a relationship with 
<taxonomicName box="[938,1070,1740,1766]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="psephota">
<emphasis box="[938,1070,1740,1766]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">L. psephota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A full description is provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kantvilas, G." box="[136,328,1776,1802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" pagination="349 - 364" refId="ref7624" refString="Kantvilas, G. (2014) New species of the genus Rimularia Nyl. from Tasmania. Lichenologist 46: 349 - 364. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282913000595" type="journal article" year="2014">Kantvilas (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
